功能。 </p><div id="d8657340333748259de7001141a938a7"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/e8jv24NjOWQ?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen scrolling="no"></iframe></div></div><p>这意味着桌面客户端中内置的一些新功能也已在<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/steam-deck/">Steam Deck</a>上可用。具体来说，Valve 提到了客户对游戏内叠加层的彻底修改——除了新界面和更通用的工具栏外，玩家现在还可以使用跨 PC 同步的新笔记工具。得益于新框架，此功能现在可同时在桌面和 Steam Deck 上使用。叠加层还有一个新的“pin”功能，允许用户在游戏过程中保持该笔记工具（或游戏界面中的任何其他窗口）可见。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Valve 还试图清理客户的通知。单击该图标现在应该只显示最近和相关的通知，并会提示用户单击以查看完整的历史视图。用户也应该看到客户端其余部分的小更新，包括更新的对话框文本、新字体和调整的颜色。</p><p>新功能很不错，但 Valve 似乎最自豪的是它在引擎盖下所做的改进。除了新框架外，该公司还表示，它还为 Mac 和 Linux 用户启用了硬件加速，从而在所有平台上提供更流畅的体验。</p><p>最后，也许也是最不重要的一点，更新可能是旧版 Steam Big Picture 模式的终结。在客户端的一长串错误修复中，隐藏着一条注释，即启用“oldbigpicture”的命令行选项已被删除。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/valve-big-picture-steam-deck-114113851.html">我们现在都在使用 Steam Deck 界面</a>。</p><p>新的 Steam 客户端更新现已可供下载。查看<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0b3JlLnN0ZWFtcG93ZXJlZC5jb20vbmV3cy9hcHAvNTkzMTEwL3ZpZXcvMzY4NzkzMTk2NTU5ODMyMzQzNiIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZmFhMjViYmYtNDk2MC00YTAxLThjOGItMTBkMGIxYmQ3YjUwIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAZpbu9qrcmRGm-wGfM8ZlczTnnMSgyCZGs8iGdEchyM-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstore.steampowered.com%2Fnews%2Fapp%2F593110%2Fview%2F3687931965598323436" class="rapid-with-clickid">完整的补丁说明</a>以了解详细信息。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/steam-overhauls-notifications-ui-elements-and-the-in-game-overlay-000839366.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/steam-overhauls-notifications-ui-elements-and-the-in-game-overlay-000839366.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> faa25bbf-4960-4a01-8c8b-10d0b1bd7b50</guid><dc:creator>肖恩·巴克利</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 15 Jun 2023 00:08:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686787714</ingested><modified> 2023-06-15T00:08:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sean Buckley]]></category><media:content height="2161" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6e60f640-0b0e-11ee-bf6f-5663b25624e2" width="3841"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2161" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/6e60f640-0b0e-11ee-bf6f-5663b25624e2" width="3841"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Valve]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Steam now has an improved in-game overlay.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Valve has updated the Steam Desktop Client]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Senate bill would hold AI companies liable for harmful content]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>政客们认为他们有办法让公司对<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-is-suddenly-everywhere-are-we-ready-180031821.html">麻烦的生成人工智能</a>负责：取消他们的法律保护。参议员 Richard Blumenthal 和 Josh Hawley <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.hawley.senate.gov/hawley-blumenthal-introduce-bipartisan-legislation-protect-consumers-and-deny-ai-companies-section#">提出了</a>一项 AI 无第 230 条豁免权法案，顾名思义，该法案将阻止 OpenAI、谷歌和类似公司使用《通信规范法案》的第 230 条免除对有害内容的责任并避免诉讼。例如，如果有人创建了深度伪造的图像或<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-voice-tool-deepfake-celebrity-audio-clips-094648743.html">声音片段</a>来破坏声誉，则工具开发人员可能会与使用它的人一起承担责任。</p><p>霍利将该法案描述为迫使人工智能创造者在开发产品时“对商业决策负责”。他还将立法视为制定人工智能规则和建立安全措施的“第一步”。在本周关于 AI 对人权影响的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.judiciary.senate.gov/committee-activity/hearings/artificial-intelligence-and-human-rights">听证会上</a>，Blumenthal 敦促国会拒绝 AI 广泛的第 230 条保障措施，这些保障措施保护社交网络免受法律后果。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> 5 月，Blumenthal 和 Hawley 举行了听证会，OpenAI 负责人 Sam Altman 等发言人呼吁政府对人工智能采取行动。行业领导者已经敦促<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tech-leaders-and-ai-experts-demand-a-six-month-pause-on-out-of-control-ai-experiments-114553864.html">暂停 AI 实验</a>，并且最近将不受控制的 AI 的威胁与<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ai-presents-risk-of-extinction-on-par-with-nuclear-war-industry-leaders-say-114025874.html">核战争</a>的威胁进行了比较。</p><p>多年来，国会一直在推动<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-energy-and-commerce-section-230-hearing-181054717.html">第 230 条改革</a>，以控制科技公司，尤其是担心互联网巨头可能故意允许有害内容。如果企业故意使用<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-bill-justice-against-malicious-algorithms-act-162915185.html">造成情感或身体伤害的算法，</a> 2021 年的众议院法案将追究企业的责任。不过，这些法案已经停滞不前，而第 230 条仍然完好无损。立法者在设定<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/why-lawmakers-are-pushing-age-verification-requirements-for-social-media-platforms-190037563.html">年龄验证要求方面</a>取得了更大的成功，理论上可以减少年轻用户的心理健康问题。</p><p>目前尚不清楚该法案是否有更大的成功机会。 Blumenthal 和 Hawley 因推出未能获得关注的在线内容法案而闻名，例如以儿童安全为导向的<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/earn-it-act-2022-explained-153058123.html">EARN IT 法案</a>和 Hawley 的反成瘾<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-07-30-senate-bill-bans-addictive-social-network-features.html">SMART 法案</a>。除了说服其他参议员外，他们还需要一项同样在众议院通过投票的等效法案。</p><p></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/senate-bill-would-hold-ai-companies-liable-for-harmful-content-212340911.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/senate-bill-would-hold-ai-companies-liable-for-harmful-content-212340911.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 445bbefd-bc32-4686-a862-7b086cc40481</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 14 Jun 2023 21:23:40 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686777822</ingested><modified> 2023-06-14T21:23:46+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2425" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/b9ca4b70-0af2-11ee-b3be-f20cc9508861" width="3637"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2425" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/b9ca4b70-0af2-11ee-b3be-f20cc9508861" width="3637"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Elizabeth Frantz / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[U.S. Senator Josh Hawley (R-MO) listens during a Senate Judiciary